This is due to the struct being nil
```go
func (l *limiter) topicCollector(topic string) (*leakybucket.Collector, error) {
	l.RLock()
```
the `l` struct is nil, so calling l.topicCollector will lead to a panic. This is due to the cleanup function of the sync service:
```go
func (s *Service) Stop() error {
	defer func() {
		if s.rateLimiter != nil {
			s.rateLimiter.free()
			s.rateLimiter = nil
		}
	}()
	defer s.cancel()
	return nil
}
```
